
[1]coldness

   COLDNESS, n.

   1. Want of heat; as the coldness or water or air. When the heat or
   temperature of any substance is less than that of the animal body
   exposed to it, that state or temperature is called coldness.

   2. Unconcern; indifference; a frigid state of temper; want of ardor,
   zeal, emotion, animation, or spirit; negligence; as, to receive an
   answer with coldness; to listen with coldness.

   3. Want of apparent affection, or kindness; as, to receive a friend
   with coldness.

   4. Coyness; reserve; indifference; as, to receive addresses with
   coldness.

   5. Want of sensual desire; frigidity; chastity.
